Reasoning: 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on improving software cost models through feature selection. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper compares different feature selection methods and uses them to estimate software development effort. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with improving the accuracy and robustness of software cost models, which can be seen as an AI problem. 
- cs.SD (Software Development) is a relevant category as the paper deals with software development effort estimation. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is less likely but still possible as the paper may involve programming languages and their impact on software cost models.
